Citation.sAbstract: Experimental VLE data at 313.15K for the ternary system TAME+ methanol + hexane are reported. A static method using an isothermal total pressure cell (Van Ness  technique) has been employed. Reduction of the experimental data has been done by Barker s method using Wohl expansion, NRTL, Wilson and UNIQUAC equations. Moreover, experimental results have been compared to predictions for the ternary system obtained from its corresponding binaries from Wilson, NRTL and UNIQUAC models.
Citation.sTitle: Vapour liquid equilibrium of octane enhancing additives in gasolines 7: Total pressure data and gE for the ternary mixture tert-amyl methyl ether (TAME), methanol and hexane at 313.15K
